Java Arrays Methods Cheat Sheet
| Method                  | Purpose                          | Example                        | Output                 | When to Use           |
| ----------------------- | -------------------------------- | ------------------------------ | ---------------------- | --------------------- |
| `Arrays.sort()`         | Sorts array in ascending order   | `Arrays.sort(arr)`             | Sorted array           | Sorting data          |
| `Arrays.binarySearch()` | Searches element in sorted array | `Arrays.binarySearch(arr, 30)` | Index of element       | Fast searching        |
| `Arrays.equals()`       | Compares two arrays              | `Arrays.equals(arr1, arr2)`    | `true/false`           | Array comparison      |
| `Arrays.fill()`         | Fills array with same value      | `Arrays.fill(arr, 10)`         | All elements become 10 | Initialization        |
| `Arrays.copyOf()`       | Copies array with new size       | `Arrays.copyOf(arr, 5)`        | New array              | Clone/resize array    |
| `Arrays.copyOfRange()`  | Copies specific range            | `Arrays.copyOfRange(arr,1,4)`  | Partial array          | Extract sub-array     |
| `Arrays.toString()`     | Converts array to String         | `Arrays.toString(arr)`         | `[10, 20, 30]`         | Printing arrays       |
| `Arrays.deepToString()` | Prints multidimensional arrays   | `Arrays.deepToString(arr)`     | Nested output          | 2D/3D arrays          |
| `Arrays.stream()`       | Creates stream from array        | `Arrays.stream(arr)`           | Stream object          | Java 8 operations     |
| `Arrays.asList()`*      | Converts array to List           | `Arrays.asList(arr)`           | List                   | Collection conversion |
| `Arrays.mismatch()`     | Finds first different index      | `Arrays.mismatch(arr1,arr2)`   | Index                  | Compare arrays        |
| `Arrays.parallelSort()` | Parallel sorting                 | `Arrays.parallelSort(arr)`     | Sorted array           | Large arrays          |
| `Arrays.setAll()`       | Set values using lambda          | `Arrays.setAll(arr,i->i*2)`    | Updated array          | Java 8 initialization |
